Maureen is a distributed machine learning library for Python.  It is built on top of mrjob library which provides a MapReduce framework in Python.

Maureen is currently in pre-release development.  

Goals for the 0.1 release:
-install not difficult
-recommendation engine works on distributed system

Feature Request List
Recommendation engines 
-binary ratings
-numerical ratings
-performance metrics

Clustering 
-Canopy Clustering
-LDA

Graph Analysis
-graph partitioning
-?

Classification
-SVM

Adapters to common datasets
-Movie Lens
-Wikipedia snapshot
-US Census 

Search?
